name: Zombie Scavengers Game - Renton, WA
description:
CAN YOU SURVIVE THE ZOMBIE APOCALYPSE?

Zombie Scavengers leads you into the city to collect supplies to survive during this interactive scavenger game.

With the whole world in chaos and zombies outnumbering the living 10 to 1, small colonies of the living are doing all they can to survive. Using your smartphone, your team will be tasked with scavenging the city for food, supplies, weapons, and shelter. The more things you find, the more points you get and more likely you are to survive. Along the way, you will be asked to do a challenge or answer a trivia question in order to be rewarded virtual weapons to ward off the zombies. The area is crawling with relentless zombies, and rival colonies are moving in. If you get too relaxed, rival colonies will take what you worked hard to find. The goal is to find all of the items in hopes that you will survive the zombie apocalypse.

name: Uncle Eddie's Public House
description: BIG. WARM. GENUINE. We're a neighborhood pub—providing a great place to eat and drink with family and friends— in the heart of South Park. Our bar crafts signature cocktails, and we offer quality well pours. Our 'Beer and a Bump' menu pairs your favorite beer with a shot of liquor for a special price. On tap, we support our local breweries and cideries with something for everyone. Our short—but excellent!—menu features grilled sandwiches, hearty salads and house-made soups. Start off right with some mac n cheese balls or mini jalapeno & cream cheese hand pies. Gluten-free bun options are available. To quote Seattle Met, “…there are satisfying sandos of every ilk” at Uncle Eddie’s, “a please-everyone type of establishment.” Weekend Brunch focuses BISCUITS! Have them smothered with your choice of honey-butter, gravy, berries or hollandaise. Enjoy them with a pounder mimosa to toast the weekend!

name: Clue-Gathering Adventure Game - Seattle, WA
description:
3Quest Challenge is a digital adventure game that takes you around the city to complete 3 Quests using your smartphone. 

You'll start out at a Home Base, then the game will lead you on 3 Quests around the city. Each Quest has 3 checkpoints. At each checkpoint, you'll answer a question to collect a clue, and then perform a challenge. For each question you answer correctly, you score a point! After you've completed the Quests, you'll come back to your Home Base to solve your final puzzle using the clues you've collected, and get even more points by solving the final puzzle correctly!

The objective is to have fun, score the most points, and correctly solve the final puzzle! You can form teams, race your friends, or just have an afternoon of fun with family and friends. Oh, and remember that you are not alone; you have a guide that is just a call or text away that can help throughout your adventure!

itemListElement.name: Wacky Adventure Walk Game - Seattle, WA

name: Wacky Adventure Walk Game - Seattle, WA
description:
Wacky Walks is a unique walking game. It is similar to a board game in which the power, or control shifts from one player to another, and instead of a board, you’ll be navigating the city streets with your smartphone to play. 

The objective of the game is to have fun, learn some facts about the city, be a little wacky, and enjoy the company of whoever you are playing with. Wacky Walks will start out by designating who will be the first King or Queen (kind of like a Team Captain), but don’t worry, that could soon change. You’ll then go out on checkpoints throughout the city. 

At each checkpoint, the players will need to answer a question about the checkpoint and the players, or “pawns” as we call them will perform a task for the King or Queen. 

Wacky Walks is done completely on foot and usually takes about two hours to complete. But don’t worry, you won’t be alone. You’ll have a remote/virtual guide that will be available in case you get stuck.

itemListElement.name: Crazy Dash Walking Adventure - Seattle, WA

name: Crazy Dash Walking Adventure - Seattle, WA
description:
Crazy Dash is a digital adventure walking tour that takes you around the city to do silly tasks and see the sights using just an app on your smartphone. These sites could range from monuments and historical markers to sculptures and other important landmarks of the city. 

The objective of the Crazy Dash is to have a blast with your friends and family, explore the city, learn a little, answer questions about your checkpoints, and complete crazy challenges. 

After getting introduced to a remote guide via text message, you'll set out to 10 checkpoints around the city. At each checkpoint, you'll answer a question. Along the way, be prepared to perform crazy tasks! You won't be alone. Your remote Guide will monitor your progress  throughout the Dash. They may even give you challenges!

itemListElement.name: Underground Donut Tour: Seattle's Only Donut Tour

name: Underground Donut Tour: Seattle's Only Donut Tour
description:
Taste some of the finest donuts that Seattle has to offer on this 2 hour Walking Tour. On this tour,

we'll make four stops at some of the best donut spots in the city. We hope you can join us.

review.name: Delicious and Delightful Donut Tour
review.reviewBody: Recently spent a lovely Sunday morning experiencing Seattle through a donut lens. Scott, our tour guide, was knowledgeable, entertaining, and warm. You immediately feel like friends. His infectious energy animates the entire tour! All food-related safety precautions were in place and, of course, we got to eat some DELICIOUS donuts. I highly recommend the tour for all ages as a fun way to explore the city. I didn't find traveling by foot overly strenuous (even in the wake of a freshly healed broken ankle). Take the weather into consideration and wear a good rain jacket like a real Seattleite. Umbrellas are for tourists, only ;-)

review.name: Delicious!
review.reviewBody: This was a fun tour with great stops for donut fans. The walking tour and history between the shops was a nice way to learn more about the area and the food was delicious.  Our guide Holly was delightful and knowledgeable. We parked near Pike Place where the tour ends which made for an easy departure. Thank you!

review.name: Pleasant side of Seattle and donuts come with the tour!
review.reviewBody: An excellent way to see some of the unique sites in Seattle. Amanda was an awesome guide as she provided donut pun throughout the tour, which really made it more interesting. Great start and end, just not where you parked unless you plan better than we did. Not a very far walk back and you do end at Pike’s Place Market. A little disappointed that we didn’t visit the mochi donut bakery, but tasting them was a treat. A very well plan  we nned and eRrxecuted tour that is a little more unique and worth the time. Wear comfortable shoes and be prepared for some steep streets. Worth the time.

itemListElement.name: One-Hour Private Seattle Sightseeing Cruise - BYOB!

name: One-Hour Private Seattle Sightseeing Cruise - BYOB!
description:
Please book as far in advance as possible as we staff based on reservations! We have 3 boats that can accommodate up to 6 guests each! You can also book individual tickets for this tour as a shared experience from our other listing "One Hour Sightseeing Cruise."
Aboard Candere you will be in the hands of a professional and in the lap of luxury. A knowledgeable tour guide skilled boat handler, your captain will introduce you to Seattle via a most enjoyable boat tour. Starting on the North side of Lake Union you will cruise by boats and floating homes of all sizes, shapes and ages. You are likely to see draw bridges that are nearly 100 years old open up for sailboats and large yachts, Seaplanes taking off and landing, locals enjoying the sunshine from kayaks and stand up paddleboards. After your journey aboard Candere, you will want to stay all day.

review.name: Awesome experience!
review.reviewBody: This experience was on we will always remember. Smooth ride, fun conversation, and learned some awesome facts about Seattle! We will have to return again! Thank you for the best day!

review.name: Great experience!
review.reviewBody: Our ride with Curt was wonderful! We really enjoyed the boat ride and his commentary. It was a perfect day to be out on the water with a cocktail. 10/10 would recommend!

review.name: Best way to see Lake Union!
review.reviewBody: Highly recommend this tour!  One of the best things we did while visiting Seattle! Our Captain/Bartender, Dylan, was a great tour guide and really nice guy.  We enjoyed being able to cruise along and see the sights, drink in hand, while hearing all about the history of Lake Union. Much better than being on a large lake cruise boat packed with tourists. Lots of fun if you’re visiting or are being a tourist in your own town.

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: We had a delightful time with Captain Curt. He was friendly and answered all questions. We didn't feel rushed or hurried at all. We had a great afternoon and family outing. I highly recommend this excursion.

review.name: Fun and memorable
review.reviewBody: Mark was great! He was really mellow, allowing us to enjoy the sights and ask questions. Thank you for this fun and memorable experience!

review.name: Great sightseeing cruise!
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful, fun experience.  Our Captain was very friendly and informative.  We got to see a different view of the lake and get close to all that was happening on it.  Only wish we had booked a longer cruise!

review.name: Amazing one hour Boat trip
review.reviewBody: Boat trip was super fun! Great view of lake and downtown Seattle. Captain/ bartender was super friendly. Drinks were delicious!

review.name: Seattle Cruise with Family!
review.reviewBody: Excellent Cruise! My family and I had a great time and the view of all Seattle was beautiful. Our guide was awesome and very pleasant. He was very informative as well. I recommend this cruise!

review.name: Such A Great Time!!!
review.reviewBody: We had such an amazing time with Amy as our captain!! She was very knowledgeable with not only the history of the area, but once she got to know us, she had much more to teach us about things she knew we would enjoy! It was like going on a boat ride with a friend! I will absolutely be booking again. The boat was comfy, the bay amazing, and again, just a wonderful afternoon with Amy on the water!!

review.name: Excellent Cruise
review.reviewBody:
Fantastic views!  
Fun Captain! 
Delicious wine. 
Waving to all the other boaters.  
Floating homes!

Excellent value

name: SPIN Seattle
description: SPIN is the original ping pong social club, your offline social network, the only one that doesn't require a membership. We encourage human connections through a game that transcends age, gender, and any boundaries. SPIN welcomes diversity and embraces the unconventional. From social gatherings to corporate events, we deliver an unparalleled experience. #UnitedByPingPong

itemListElement.name: Rent a beautifully restored VW Vanagon Westfalia camper van

name: Rent a beautifully restored VW Vanagon Westfalia camper van
description:
The 

Black Forest Westfalias experience is a 

cut above. Our 

small fleet of 4 vans is 

meticulously maintained and

 perfectly 

modified (see below) for

 Northwest adventure, from campgrounds and state parks to 

wild camping in open forest. For ten years our family has lived and breathed 

Westy camping in this region, finding those

 hidden spots and

 routes less-traveled, and now it is our great joy to 

share what we have learned with our renters. Let us outfit you with the vehicle and knowledge to go beyond. 

There is so much more to see!

review.name: Glamping with beautiful vanagon.
review.reviewBody: My husband wanted to go camping in Pacific NW.  He left the details to me and immediately, I decided if we are going to camp, we are going to glamp.  I have always wanted to try a VW vanagon, and after looking at many reviews and websites that rented VW and RVs, I decided to go with Black Forest Westfalia because it was a small family owned business with someone who seems to know and love his vans.  And Mike is exactly that when we met him.  Mike is great to work with and very knowledgeable about his vans.  His vans are clearly loved.  And we definitely loved our van Goldie.  She was a champ! We had so much fun.  Thanks, Mike. We will definitely go with Black Forest Westfalia and Mike and Goldie next time we are in the Pacific Northwest.

itemListElement.name: Full-Day Olympic National Park Tour from Seattle

name: Full-Day Olympic National Park Tour from Seattle
description:
We take you to visit Olympic National Park with visiting Hurricane Ridge, Lake Crescent and many other great wonders of the natural beauty.

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The tickets fee should pay to the tour guide in cash and the tour guide will arrange activities admissions for the group. City Passes and Annual passes are not acceptable on our tours.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

review.name: Olympic National Park Tour: Entirely Spoken in Chinese
review.reviewBody: I am not usually one to leave a review and I generally make the most out of every experience I have but this was an experience I would not recommend for certain travelers. The tour was entirely in Chinese so if you do not speak the language, I would not recommend booking this tour as there is little/no translation over the course of the 8 hour tour. A lot of time spent driving around (about 4 hours) leaving little time frames to explore the 3 destinations they take you within Olympic National Park. Don't get me wrong, there were great views but I would not want others booking this trip without knowing the language barriers that are involved with this tour group/company. I would not book this type of tour again, there may be greater ease in renting a car and exploring the park on your own!!

review.name: Bad service
review.reviewBody: No communication, no branding, 6 hours on a car and only 40 minutes on the national park. The tour guide had hard time speaking English

review.name: Amazing weather during end of August
review.reviewBody: The place is insanely beautiful and humbling. We drove to Olympic National Park Visitor Center and then further ahead to Hurrican ridge and hiked there. It wasn't a challenging hike, mostly uphill but the views are worth it.

review.name: Olympic National Park tour
review.reviewBody:
The view is spectacular - both the mountains and forests and the lake and ferry. It means specifically for us due to Twilight saga & Grey's anatomy - very special nature and climate in Seattle.

The driver/guide is friendly too - did not have the chance to say goodbye and thanks to him though. Mated with two ladies and a Russian couple - they are interesting people :)

Everything is good except for the weather.

Pricing should be clarified - it is a $100 trip - $35 of park entrance and $15 of ferry per person - but fortunately the ladies had free passing to allow the entire car in for free thus saving $210 in total - I don't know how the company manages this but should better take such situation into consideration in the future

review.name: Olympic tour
review.reviewBody: This had to be the worst tour I could imagine. 6 hours in the car for 1 hours of unstructured time at one lookout and 30 minutes at Carter Lake. We got NO information from the guide, as he didn't speak English.  The tour guide was great at informing the Chinese speakers but could not communicate in English AT ALL. It lists the tour language as English and I feel duped. Get a car and go yourself!

review.name: Beautiful trip with a wonderful guide.
review.reviewBody: Our guide Mike was a very jovial person, who made the trip very enjoyable with his anecdotes about his first hand experiences and other local knowledge. The place itself it so beautiful, it’s just not enough to visit once.

itemListElement.name: Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle

name: Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Simply put - there is no other tour like this out of Seattle! Combine the best the Northwest has to offer in this full-day adventure: a beautiful hike in the National Park with big views of Mt. Rainier, an seasonal picnic lunch outside, and wine tastings at beloved wineries in the Yakima Valley!

At the height of summer, Mount Rainier's flower-flanked trails provide the relaxation, fresh air, and peace that only comes with a walk in a quiet, wild place. Choose from a variety of trails. Our TripAdvisor "Hall of Fame" guides run the only day tours permitted to explore more than a mile from the park road as the National Park is ecologically important & delicate. We're lovely & professional nature educators (not bus drivers) that have dedicated their lives to artful travel.

Our all-inclusive small group day trip is limited to just 10 travelers. Sleep in a little - we'll bring coffee, tea, and pastries. We’ll bring snacks, water and sparkling water for the day. Don’t worry about a thing!

review.name: Wonderful day hike with a stunning sunset in the end
review.reviewBody:
Did the Telica all day hike with Guide Norlan.It was the 2.time I had him as my guide.I loved that he explained so much about plants and animals along the hike.You can really tell he loves what he does and likes to share his knowlede with others.It was a beautiful day with amazing views and it was really cool to get to a crater that close!
The sunset was a beautiful ending of a perfect hiking day!
Thank you Norlan again!

review.name: Tess was great.
review.reviewBody: Great tour. Tess was an excellent tour guide, very knowledgeable and took us to great spots. Breakfast and lunch were more than just a sandwich like most other tours. I would definitely use this company again, especially if we could get Tess again as our tour guide.

review.name: Fantastic Day
review.reviewBody:
Really an amazing experience, Karen is about as good of a guide as you can get. 

What really sets Evergreen Escapes apart from others is they take care of EVERYTHING for you: food, parking/pickup, driving, hiking gear, trail guide...just show up with a good camera and some good walking shoes and you're set. 

Do remember you're in Washington, and so weather may obscure Mt. Ranier the day you go out, but it's so beautiful out there that even without Ranier there's plenty of beauty to go around.

Wine was fantastic, food was fantastic, views were fantastic, company was fantastic, day was fantastic, worth every dollar.

review.name: Top Notch - Hiking & Wine Tasting
review.reviewBody:
What a fabulous way to spend a day in the Pacific Northwest!!!  Karen, our guide, was outstanding providing us with information and always staying ahead to make our trip enjoyable.  The picnic lunch was excellent and Karen ran ahead so that she could have it all setup for us.   And the wine tasting at 2 wineries topped off the trip nicely.  Generous pours and able to taste 6+ wines at each stop!

Vastly different landscapes make the driving (or rather, the ride) well worth it 

I would highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Memorable Day!
review.reviewBody:
Sarah, our guide, chef, and chauffeur for the day, was phenomenal !!!  She was so sweet, knowledgeable, engaging, and patient!! This tour is a great blend of activity between hiking and wine tasting .  The views all day are amazing.  My favorite part was hiking the Natchez trail on the Pacific Crest Trail with stunning views of Mt Ranier and then a fabulous lunch with grilled chicken, pesto pasta, and broccoli salad. After, we visited 2 wineries in Yakima Valley.  Fortuity winery was so fun and educational (and the wine is delish)!  There’s plenty of snacks and drinks all day. 

Tips: 1) you can hike in running shoes but hiking shoes might feel more stable . 2)Be mentally ready for lots of seat time in the van (several hours at time) between Mt Rainer and the wineries is about 2 hours and then returning to Seattle is about 3 hrs.  Still worth the time- such a memorable trip with a nice variety!!!

review.name: Breathtakingly beautiful
review.reviewBody:
What a day! This is a must do, for anyone interested in hiking, breathtaking scenery, fun, geology, geography, horticulture, foraging, wildlife, history, wine and getting in the great outdoors!
Ben was our guide, he was an encyclopedia of local knowledge, he explained so much of what we were seeing, pointed out interesting reference points, and explained about many of the wildflowers of the naches trail, which were in full bloom, and so abundant!
We could have spent all week there, the two vineyards were great too, all included in the price were the tasting room sessions, we bought a bottle from each place, owen roe and freehand cellars.
We recommend you go on evergreenescapes website to search the many tours they have available, you'll be sure to find an experience that suits anyone!
Many thanks for an unforgettable trip!

review.name: A must!
review.reviewBody: Our guide, Marjorie, was so sweet and very knowledgeable. There is a lot of driving time involved but the breathtaking views are worth it! They provided tea, coffee, hot coco and pastries at our first stop. The coffee was delicious! We then did two mini hikes (about 1 mile each) at two different locations. The hike is not rigorous although some parts are steep so just be prepared to feel the burn in those quads! After that we had a picnic style lunch and the food was delicious. We then im enjoyed sampling wine at two wineries. It was a fabulous day! Definitely my favorite part of my trip to Seattle. If you get a chance to take this tour, I highly recommend it!

review.name: Wonderful day trip to Mount Rainier and Yakima Valley
review.reviewBody: This tour was fabulous!  The Mountain was out and we got to see Rainier in all her glory.  Our guide, Kevin, was terrific.  There was a lot of snow on the mountain still so we did not get to do the regular hike but Kevin more than made that up to us with alternate stops and a hike to Silver Falls.  The provided food was delicious as well!

review.name: Not as advertised
review.reviewBody:
Several discrepancies against what was advertised.  We had a good time, until we didn’t….

First, the operator wanted us to walk a block to meet. No big deal, still optimistic 

Coffee was made available well over 1.5 hours after our pickup and there were 8 muffins for 8 guests. They were nice muffins but we ran out of coffee. There was no tea, no fruit.  One flavor of coffee sweetener. 

The mountain was gorgeously displayed as we had a perfect, clear day. But the hike was not a one mile private trail for guides. It was Naches, well over 3 hours with steep gradation.  We weren’t physically prepared and bailed at a mile. 

Lunch wasn’t until after 1 pm and was quite good, if not inclusive of any greens. 

The wineries were a long drive and we had a nice time. But we didn’t arrive home until after 9pm and there was no dinner stop (unless you were cool with the Arby’s at the Pilot gas station). 

We don’t recommend and opine we would choose. A Ranier day or a winery day.  Listening to drunk millennials sing rap on the return trip was just not for us.  

Guide was awesome but too distracted by front seat passenger. Trip home was harrowing.

review.name: Fun & Flexible
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide/driver was Kevin.  He's a regular trivia expert!  Always spouting off facts about building, roads, rivers, passes, and events.  We stopped for coffee and blueberry/banana muffins at the Federation Forest then started our van trek through Rainier National Park. For our main hike, we did some of the Pacific Crest Trail then went around Tipsoo Lake and Naches Pass. We were lucky to have a completely sunny with a high of 75 day!  Afterwards, we had a delicious meal packed by a local farm to fresh grocer. I have never had a golden beet salad so good!  The next stop would have been the Yakima Valley for wine... Unfortunately the local forest fires made that area inaccessible to tourists so we went to some local tasting rooms in Snoqualmie. Chateau Noelle and WM Grassie.  We got to sample several styles of wines from each producer and I certainly went home with a few bottles.  Our last stop was the Snoqualmie Falls.  Absolutely stunning.  After a very full day, we got dropped off and we bar hoping by 8:00.  Thanks again, Kevin!

mainEntity.name: How do I arrange pickup for the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: We offer complimentary pick-up and drop-off wherever you’re staying in downtown Seattle – hotels, Airbnbs, vacation rentals, a private home, etc. Our operations team will connect with you 24 hours prior to your trip to confirm the time and location.

mainEntity.name: What should I wear for the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: Please wear closed-toe comfortable walking shoes, hiking shoes, or boots and bring a light wind/waterproof jacket. We also recommend dressing in layers, with a non-cotton outer layer (please avoid denim).

mainEntity.name: What should I bring with me on the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: A hat and sunglasses are great. Also, your cell phone or camera and any necessary medications are pretty much it! We're happy to take care of everything else!

mainEntity.name: How many wineries do we visit on the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: We partner with wineries that paint a beautiful picture of Washington's rich heritage; we’ll visit two excellent winemakers east of the tallest mountain in Washington!

mainEntity.name: Which wineries are visited during the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: Your guide will combine group preferences, weather considerations, and more to create a lovely day. We're likely to change wineries from day to day to give you the best possible experience. If you have a winery in mind, please let your guide know.

mainEntity.name: Do you have vegetarian options on the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: Yes - Please be sure to enter in any special needs/requests in the "Special Requirements" box at checkout and we will do our best to accommodate you!

mainEntity.name: How strenuous is the Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: We have built our trips to appeal to all abilities and interest levels, and are rated easy to moderate. Our tours have a maximum of ten guests, which allows your guide to tailor the activity level to your group.

mainEntity.name: What happens if it rains on the day of my Hike Mt. Rainier & Taste Yakima Valley Wine: All-Inclusive Day Tour from Seattle?

acceptedAnswer.text: Our guides craft the best itinerary to accommodate the weather. We run our tours rain or shine because the Pacific Northwest is stunning regardless of the weather. Frequently, wet weather only lasts an hour or so before things start to improve again!

itemListElement.name: Half-Day Private Seattle Highlights Tour up to 12 Pax, Includes Cruise Transfer

name: Half-Day Private Seattle Highlights Tour up to 12 Pax, Includes Cruise Transfer
description:
Pack Seattle’s highlights into a manageable 4-hour private tour. Explore Seattle's top city highlights including the Space Needle, Pike Place Market, the Chihuly Glass Museum, Kerry Park and Lake Union. We’ll not only transfer your group up to 12 passengers, but take care of your luggage too if you’ve got it in tow. At the end of the tour, we’ll transfer you at your hotel, cruise terminal or the airport as needed.

-Customizable Private Guided Tour for up to 12 people
-Explore Seattle’s top attractions on foot—not just a drive-by for a blurry photo 
-Complimentary private transfer for your group between cruise ship, Seattle hotel, or Sea-Tac airport
-Visit Pike Place Market, Space Needle, Seattle’s #1 postcard photo spot at Kerry Park and Gas Works Park to marvel at the house boat communities on Lake Union

itemListElement.name: Mt. Rainier National Park Tour from Seattle

name: Mt. Rainier National Park Tour from Seattle
description:
Go to Mt. Rainier to see the tallest volcano of the continental United States by visiting Christine Falls, Narada Falls, and Paradise Road.

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The tickets fee should pay to the tour guide in cash and the tour guide will arrange activities admissions for the group. City Passes and Annual passes are not acceptable on our tours.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

review.name: Great value
review.reviewBody: We went on Friday Nov 5. Took a minivan with Olympic National Park tourists for about half an hour then transeferred to another minivan. Only five of us in the minivan: the friendly driver/tour guide, another couple, and us. Great views of falls and Mt Rainier! The Paradise Inn Visitor Center was closed.

review.name: They did their best
review.reviewBody: We went to tour on June 25, due to several people cancelled tour that day, we saw three young guides teamed up, they helped each other, reorganized the vehicles quickly and got tour starting as soon as possible. Our guide was Chris, very young but pretty knowledgeable, good driving skill let us feel safe. He introduced many things on the way to Rainer park, and gave us enough time to stay  at Paradise site. Thanks for Chris.

name: Seattle Sites and Snoqualmie Falls Tour
description: Seattle, all the sights and sounds, plus Snoqualmie Falls. You'll travel in our comfortable SUV with 5 guests max. Usually it's just you. Discover Seattle's popular downtown attractions in style.

name: Holly Jolly Hunt - Seattle, WA
description: Holly Jolly Hunt is a holiday scavenger hunt done on your smartphone, that brings your entire family and friends together for holiday cheer. During the adventure you’ll be seeking out all the traditional, and even the non-traditional holiday items we all see this time of year. You’ll use the app to get points for each item you find. The goal is to capture as many items as you can in order to score as many points as you can. Along the way you’ll be asked to perform silly holiday themed tasks meant to bring laughter and smiles to everyone involved. Come play with us. Young or old, this is a scavenger hunt for everyone that enjoys this time of year. Holly Jolly Hunt is back for 2018 and we promise you will create holiday memories that you will not forget!

name: Communal: 9-course, three-hour tasting menu tour
description:
Check availability for your 9-course walking tour between appetizer, entree, and dessert at three of the cities' most desirable restaurants that happens on the 3rd Wednesday of each month. On our tour, you'll meet new friends as we highlight the flavors and spice that make each Seattle neighborhood unique. This is a three-hour experience and no tiny bites here, you'll have enough for a full meal. 

Have a group of 6 or more? Look at our Exclusive tasting menu tours where you have your pick of the day and neighborhood. 

We are defining the dining experience through public and private reservations in Seattle and the Pacific Northwest. Founders Joey Manley and Michael Watts have built ties with the premier restaurants and chefs in the region to create custom menus tailored to each guest for a truly carefree dining experience.

itemListElement.name: Private Pike Place Market Spice Tour and Workshop with a Chef

name: Private Pike Place Market Spice Tour and Workshop with a Chef
description:
Enjoy a private and fun-filled spice workshop and tour while you're in Seattle during this interactive food experience with a local chef! Your host Kausar is delighted to share her knowledge of South Asian spices and how they can invigorate Pacific Northwest ingredients during this Pike Place Market spice workshop. After a quick walk exploring and purchasing bread, seasonal produce and cheese from favored vendors at Pike Place outdoor Market, head over to World Spice to immerse yourself in the world of spices, specifically from South Asia. Learn about and pound your own spice blends and enjoy them in chai and a savory sandwich prepared from local ingredients.

• Discover Pacific Northwest produce and purchase ingredients together at Pike Place Market
• Learn about spices and make your own spice blends
• Enjoy a light meal of a local and seasonal salad, sandwich and chai
• Introduction to a blend of Pacific Northwest and South Asian culture and cuisine
• 100% private activity

review.name: Extremely unhappy and disappointed with cancellation 5 minutes before tour was to begin
review.reviewBody: My friend and I had booked this tour three weeks ago and had been looking forward to it.  We arrived at the meeting place only to be told it was canceled five minutes before the tour was to begin. This was unacceptable as we are both not from Seattle and had planned our entire day around this. We should have had more advanced notice so that we had planned an alternative activity. It is unconscionable to treat clients this way
